<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[264,1324,284,1870]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Remarks</emphasis>
: The only other described species of the genus is 
<taxonomicName authority="Kensley, 1978" authorityName="Kensley" authorityYear="1978" class="Malacostraca" family="Expanathuridae" genus="Rhiganthura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novaezealandiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Rhiganthura novaezealandiae</emphasis>
Kensley, 
<number box="[433,492,1724,1750]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[565,727,1724,1750]" name="New Zealand" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. The two species are very similar but the new one differs in the possession of a 
<number box="[615,624,1764,1790]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
­articulate mandibular palp (
<number box="[968,983,1764,1790]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
articles in the 
<typeStatus box="[1162,1212,1764,1790]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
species), and a visible terminal article of the maxillipedal palp. There may be differences in the uropods and telson but Kensley’s (
<number box="[630,691,1844,1870]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" value="1978.0">1978</number>
a) figures are not sufficiently detailed.
</paragraph>
